## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of education in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Education is the bounded learning-continuity structure
through which instruction,
training,
evaluation,
progression,
and capability development
become meaningful.

Education is not identical to skill.
Education shapes or certifies capability,
while skill expresses usable capability in context.

## architectural_position
Education sits between:
- life continuity
- skill development
- job eligibility
- social/cultural formation
- institutional review and credential meaning

## required_behavior
- education context must remain explicit
- learning/evaluation basis must remain explicit
- current and historical education states must remain distinguishable
- progress and certification meaning must remain explicit

## canonical_rules
- participation does not imply completion
- completion does not imply unrestricted authority
- historical education trace must remain queryable
- ambiguous education scope fails closed

## state_model
The education domain distinguishes:
- enrolled education state
- active learning state
- evaluated state
- completed state
- restricted state
- historical education state

## review_checklist
- education context is explicit
- learning/evaluation basis is explicit
- completion meaning is explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
